context_meta.title: Producer Simon Kinberg Hopes to Start Filming Channing Tatum's 'Gambit' This Summer
context_meta.summary: At Monday's New York premiere of “Deadpool 2,” producer Simon Kinberg revealed the status of another highly anticipated film: “Gambit,” starring Channing Tatum. “We have a script that we love — that Channing loves,” Kinberg told Variety on the red carpet. “We've met with a bunch of directors in the last couple of weeks, and we're hoping to actually pick one in the next couple of weeks and shoot the movie maybe the end of this summer.” Since 20th Century Fox announced “Gambit,” the project has undergone multiple developmental setbacks. In September 2015, Rupert Wyatt, who was originally slated to direct, left the film due to a timing conflict resulting from a delay in the production schedule.

context_meta.title: Tom Cruise's 'Mission: Impossible Fallout' Might Be Summer's Breakout Smash
context_meta.summary: Paramount/Viacom Inc. just dropped a new poster for Mission: Impossible Fallout, with word that we’re getting a new trailer on Wednesday. It’s no secret that I think the first Mission: Impossible Fallout trailer, released on Super Bowl Sunday, is the best trailer of 2018 by a healthy margin. If Ghost Protocol was something of a Casino Royale­-style comeback for the long-running series, then Fallout could very well be its Skyfall (or Fast Five), complete with an even-further emphasis on an ensemble for the once "Tom Cruise: Lone Wolf" action franchise.
